The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Rafique fined 

Dhaka: Bangladeshs leading bowler Mohammed Rafique was fined 75 per cent of his match-fee after a verbal duel with coach Dav Whatmore during the ongoing tour of Sri Lanka, the Bangladesh Cricket Board said Thursday. 

Rafique had arguments with Whatmore over his knee injury during a practice session in Colombo. The management of the touring team fined him 75 per cent of his match-fee of the next Test he plays for Bangladesh after conducting a hearing on Tuesday, a BCB spokesman said. (AFP) 




